Architecture plan for Issue #133: Remove footer Discord link and point the X icon to the real profile

Project structure:
- frontend/: Vite + React SPA. The footer UI is implemented in frontend/src/App.tsx, with styling in frontend/src/styles.css.
- backend/: Rust Axum API and static frontend host. No backend/API changes are needed for this issue.
- shared/: shared TypeScript constants and DTOs. No shared contract changes are needed.

Issue dependencies:
- Issue #133 is standalone and only depends on the existing SiteFooter component from prior UI work.

Implementation plan:
- Update SiteFooter in frontend/src/App.tsx.
- Remove the Discord social anchor and inline SVG entirely.
- Change the X social anchor from its placeholder/hash link to https://x.com/TheLastHN.
- Ensure the X link opens in a new tab with rel="noreferrer" and target="_blank".
- Keep product branding from PRODUCT.md and existing shared constants; do not rename the product.

Validation:
- Run TypeScript/build checks for the frontend through npm scripts.
- Confirm footer still renders and no stale Discord reference remains in the footer markup.
